  <folder name="Views" id="folder-views" type="diagrams">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:ArchimateDiagramModel" name="LGAM Layered View" id="view-lgam-layered">
      <documentation>A layered view showing all LGAM elements grouped by layer. Use this as a starting point - replace generic elements with your council's specific systems.</documentation>
    </element>
  </folder>
  <purpose>Local Government Architecture Model (LGAM) template for ArchiMate modelling.

This template provides the LGAM layer structure and reference elements as a starting point for councils to model their own technology architecture.

LGAM Layers mapped to ArchiMate:
- Public Channels = Business Interface
- Council Interfaces = Application Interface
- Capabilities = Application Service / Component
- Business Areas = Business Process
- Corporate Areas = Business Function
- Foundational Technology = Node, Technology Service
- Integration = Application Component, Path
- Security = Technology Service (cross-cutting)
- Data and Information = Data Object

Instructions:
1. Duplicate elements and rename to your council's specific systems
2. Draw relationships between elements (use Serving, Realization, Flow, Access)
3. Create views for specific business areas or technology domains
4. Remove elements that don't apply to your council

More information: https://architecture.cddo.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/gds-local/</purpose>
</archimate:model>
